# Navit C/C++: format before commit

After editing `*.c`, `*.h`, or `*.cpp` under `navit/` (except `navit/support/`, `navit/fib-1.1/`, `navit/traffic/permanentrestrictions/`), run:

```bash
clang-format -i path/to/changed_file.c
```

Config: `navit/.clang-format` (120 columns, indent 4, attach braces). CI runs the same via `scripts/ci_sanity_checks.sh`.
